main event: A UFO sighting occurred in Rehoboth, Massachusetts on March 26, 1966, where an oblong orange or amber object was observed for about 10 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed to be brightly lit on one side before fading away,No photograph was included with the report,There were multiple witnesses who described similar sightings of unidentified objects in the area,The investigation suggested that the sighting could be attributed to normal air traffic due to nearby landing lights,An analysis pointed out a concentration of light sources near the sighting location.
sighted object: oblong, brightly lit object, orange or amber in color
witness description: Local residents and individuals involved in various occupations, including postal workers and high school students, who observed the object at different times and locations.
